<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Diabetes reversal — Doctor Farmer | My Health School</title>

  <!-- Single Google Font, two weights only (400 / 600). Only external dependency. -->
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link
    href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;600&display=swap"
    rel="stylesheet"
  />

  <style>
    /* ============================================================
       DESIGN TOKENS
       Soft clinical palette: whites, deep trustworthy teal accent,
       muted greys for body text. Green reserved for "for you" checks.
       ============================================================ */
    :root {
      --accent:        #0d6e6e;  /* deep trustworthy teal — primary */
      --accent-dark:   #0a5757;  /* button active / hover */
      --ink:           #1f2a2e;  /* near-black headings */
      --body:          #4a585d;  /* muted grey body text */
      --muted:         #79878d;  /* lighter muted (captions, risk lines) */
      --good:          #1f8a4c;  /* green — positive checkmarks only */
      --soft-grey:     #6b7378;  /* "not for you" muted text + ✕ */
      --line:          #e3e8ea;  /* 0.5px borders */
      --bg:            #ffffff;  /* page background */
      --bg-soft:       #f5f8f8;  /* placeholder boxes */
      --card-bg:       #ffffff;
      --radius:        12px;
      --maxw:          720px;    /* focused single column */
    }

    * { box-sizing: border-box; }

    html { -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%; }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI',
                   Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
      font-weight: 400;
      font-size: 17px;            /* >=16px on mobile */
      line-height: 1.65;
      color: var(--body);
      background: var(--bg);
      -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
      text-rendering: optimizeLegibility;
    }

    /* Single centered column, generous side padding on small screens */
    .wrap {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: var(--maxw);
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 0 20px;
    }

    /* Vertical rhythm between sections */
    section { padding: 40px 0; }
    section:first-of-type { padding-top: 32px; }

    /* ---------- Typography ---------- */
    h1, h2, h3 {
      color: var(--ink);
      font-weight: 600;
      line-height: 1.3;
      margin: 0 0 14px;
    }
    h1 { font-size: 1.62rem; letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
    h2 { font-size: 1.32rem; }
    h3 { font-size: 1.12rem; }

    p { margin: 0 0 16px; }
    p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

    .subhead {
      font-weight: 400;
      font-size: 1.08rem;
      color: var(--body);
      margin: 0 0 24px;
    }

    .caption {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.55;
    }

    .center { text-align: center; }

    /* ============================================================
       PLACEHOLDER BOXES (video + images)
       Clean flat grey boxes, clearly labelled for later phases.
       ============================================================ */
    .placeholder {
      background: var(--bg-soft);
      border: 1px dashed var(--line);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 16px;
    }

    /* Responsive 16:9 video container */
    .video-frame {
      position: relative;
      width: 100%;
      aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
      margin: 8px 0 12px;
    }
    .video-frame .placeholder {
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 14px;
    }
    .play-icon {
      width: 64px;
      height: 64px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: #ffffff;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
    }
    .play-icon svg { display: block; }

    /* ============================================================
       CTA BUTTONS
       Solid accent, white text, large tap target (>=50px tall).
       ============================================================ */
    .cta {
      display: block;
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 360px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      min-height: 54px;
      padding: 15px 24px;
      background: var(--accent);
      color: #ffffff;
      font-family: inherit;
      font-size: 1.08rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      text-align: center;
      text-decoration: none;
      border: none;
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      cursor: pointer;
      line-height: 1.3;
      transition: background-color 0.15s ease;
    }
    .cta:hover  { background: var(--accent-dark); }
    .cta:active { background: var(--accent-dark); }

    .risk-line {
      max-width: 420px;
      margin: 14px auto 0;
      text-align: center;
    }

    /* ============================================================
       PROOF CARDS
       ============================================================ */
    .cards {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 16px;
      margin-top: 8px;
    }
    .card {
      background: var(--card-bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      padding: 18px;
    }
    .card .img-placeholder {
      height: 120px;
      margin-bottom: 14px;
    }
    .card-name {
      color: var(--ink);
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }
    .card p { font-size: 0.98rem; }

    /* The before -> after stat, made prominent */
    .stat {
      display: block;
      color: var(--accent);
      font-weight: 600;
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      margin: 12px 0;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    }
    .stat .arrow {
      margin: 0 6px;
      font-weight: 400;
    }

    .cards-footer {
      max-width: 560px;
      margin: 22px auto 0;
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      color: var(--body);
    }

    /* ============================================================
       WHO THIS IS FOR — two blocks
       ============================================================ */
    .qualify-block { margin-bottom: 28px; }
    .qualify-list {
      list-style: none;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
    }
    .qualify-list li {
      display: flex;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 12px;
      margin-bottom: 14px;
      font-size: 1.02rem;
    }
    .qualify-list li:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

    /* Green check (for you) */
    .mark {
      flex: 0 0 auto;
      width: 22px;
      height: 22px;
      margin-top: 2px;
    }
    .mark--good { color: var(--good); }

    /* Muted ✕ (not for you) — soft grey, never red */
    .mark--no { color: var(--soft-grey); }

    /* "Not for you" block reads quieter so the eye lands on block A */
    .qualify-block--no h3 { color: var(--soft-grey); }
    .qualify-block--no .qualify-list li { color: var(--soft-grey); }

    .qualify-footer {
      max-width: 520px;
      margin: 4px auto 0;
      text-align: center;
      color: var(--body);
    }

    /* ============================================================
       ABOUT THE DOCTOR
       ============================================================ */
    .doctor-photo {
      width: 100%;
      height: 220px;
      margin-bottom: 22px;
    }

    /* ============================================================
       FAQ — native details/summary accordion (pure HTML/CSS)
       ============================================================ */
    .faq {
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .faq details {
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    }
    .faq details:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

    .faq summary {
      list-style: none;
      cursor: pointer;
      padding: 18px 46px 18px 18px;
      position: relative;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--ink);
      font-size: 1.02rem;
      line-height: 1.45;
    }
    .faq summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }

    /* + / − indicator */
    .faq summary::after {
      content: "+";
      position: absolute;
      right: 18px;
      top: 16px;
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      font-weight: 400;
      color: var(--accent);
      line-height: 1;
    }
    .faq details[open] summary::after { content: "\2212"; } /* minus */

    .faq .answer {
      padding: 0 18px 18px;
      font-size: 0.98rem;
      color: var(--body);
    }

    /* ============================================================
       FINAL CTA
       ============================================================ */
    .final-cta h2 {
      max-width: 600px;
      margin: 0 auto 24px;
      text-align: center;
    }

    /* Thin divider between major sections */
    .divider {
      height: 1px;
      background: var(--line);
      border: none;
      max-width: var(--maxw);
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    /* ============================================================
       DESKTOP / WIDER VIEWPORTS
       ============================================================ */
    @media (min-width: 680px) {
      body { font-size: 18px; }
      h1 { font-size: 2.1rem; }
      h2 { font-size: 1.6rem; }
      section { padding: 52px 0; }

      /* Proof cards become a row of three */
      .cards {
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        gap: 18px;
      }
      .card .img-placeholder { height: 100px; }
      .stat { font-size: 1.15rem; }

      .doctor-photo { height: 300px; }
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>

  <!-- =========================================================
       SECTION 1 — ABOVE THE FOLD
       ========================================================= -->
  <section class="wrap" id="hero">
    <h1>Why do your diabetes tablets keep increasing — every single year?</h1>
    <p class="subhead">
      Doctor Farmer explains the real reason — and how his patients reduced
      their sugar and stopped their tablets within 6 months.
    </p>

    <!-- PHASE 2 will replace this static placeholder with the real video player
         (seek-bar lock + watch-time tracking). Keep id="vsl-video". -->
    <div class="video-frame">
      <div class="placeholder" id="vsl-video">
        <span class="play-icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="var(--accent)">
            <path d="M8 5v14l11-7z" />
          </svg>
        </span>
        <span>[VSL video — Phase 2]</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="caption">
      Watch the full video before you do anything else. What Doctor Farmer
      reveals here, most doctors will never tell you in a 7-minute consultation.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- =========================================================
       SECTION 2 — PRIMARY CTA
       ========================================================= -->
  <section class="wrap" id="primary-cta">
    <!-- PHASE 3 will wire this to the ₹99 booking form + Meta pixel / CAPI events.
         Non-functional for now. Keep id="cta-primary". -->
    <a href="#" class="cta" id="cta-primary">Book my health assessment — ₹99</a>

    <p class="caption risk-line">
      Fully refunded if our advisor says you're not a fit to our approach.
      This call is to understand your body and to give the right support.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <!-- =========================================================
       SECTION 3 — PROOF CARDS
       ========================================================= -->
  <section class="wrap" id="proof">
    <h2 class="center">Real people. Real blood reports. Real results.</h2>

    <div class="cards">

      <!-- Card 1 -->
      <article class="card">
        <!-- PHASE 2/3: real before/after HbA1c report image goes here -->
        <div class="placeholder img-placeholder">[Blood report — before/after]</div>
        <p class="card-name">Rajan, 47 — software professional, Chennai</p>
        <p>Diabetes for 8 years. Was on Metformin twice a day plus one more tablet.</p>
        <span class="stat">HbA1c: 9.2 <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span> 5.8</span>
        <p>Today: all tablets stopped. Still eats rice. Still works long days.</p>
      </article>

      <!-- Card 2 -->
      <article class="card">
        <!-- PHASE 2/3: real before/after HbA1c report image goes here -->
        <div class="placeholder img-placeholder">[Blood report — before/after]</div>
        <p class="card-name">Meenakshi, 52 — homemaker, Coimbatore</p>
        <p>Diabetes for 11 years. Was on insulin, 20 units every night.</p>
        <span class="stat">HbA1c brought down to 6.3</span>
        <p>Today: insulin stopped in 5 months.</p>
      </article>

      <!-- Card 3 -->
      <article class="card">
        <!-- PHASE 2/3: real before/after HbA1c report image goes here -->
        <div class="placeholder img-placeholder">[Blood report — before/after]</div>
        <p class="card-name">Senthil, 44 — business owner, Madurai</p>
        <p>Always travelling, eating outside, constant stress.</p>
        <span class="stat">HbA1c: 10.8 <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span> 6.1</span>
        <p>Today: three tablets reduced to one.</p>
      </article>

    </div>

    <p class="cards-footer">
      These are not exceptional cases. This is what happens when the root cause
      is addressed — not just the symptoms.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <!-- =========================================================
       SECTION 4 — WHO THIS IS FOR
       ========================================================= -->
  <section class="wrap" id="qualify">

    <!-- Block A — for you -->
    <div class="qualify-block">
      <h3>This is for you if…</h3>
      <ul class="qualify-list">
        <li>
          <svg class="mark mark--good" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"
               stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.4" stroke-linecap="round"
               stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
          </svg>
          <span>You have been managing Type 2 diabetes for at least one year.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <svg class="mark mark--good" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"
               stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.4" stroke-linecap="round"
               stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
          </svg>
          <span>Your tablets or insulin keep increasing, with no end in sight.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <svg class="mark mark--good" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"
               stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.4" stroke-linecap="round"
               stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
          </svg>
          <span>You are tired of "just manage it" and want to know if reducing
                your sugar is actually possible.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <svg class="mark mark--good" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"
               stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.4" stroke-linecap="round"
               stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
          </svg>
          <span>You are willing to be consistent — not looking for a shortcut.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Block B — not for you (intentionally quieter) -->
    <div class="qualify-block qualify-block--no">
      <h3>This is not for you if…</h3>
      <ul class="qualify-list">
        <li>
          <svg class="mark mark--no" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"
               stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.4" stroke-linecap="round"
               stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M6 6l12 12M18 6L6 18" />
          </svg>
          <span>You are looking for a magic tablet or an overnight fix.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <svg class="mark mark--no" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"
               stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.4" stroke-linecap="round"
               stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M6 6l12 12M18 6L6 18" />
          </svg>
          <span>You are not willing to make small, daily changes for a few months.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <svg class="mark mark--no" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"
               stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.4" stroke-linecap="round"
               stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M6 6l12 12M18 6L6 18" />
          </svg>
          <span>You believe tablets alone will solve the problem, without any
                lifestyle change.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="qualify-footer">
      We are honest about who we can help. If you are serious, we would like
      to speak with you.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <!-- =========================================================
       SECTION 5 — ABOUT THE DOCTOR
       ========================================================= -->
  <section class="wrap" id="about">
    <h2>Who is Doctor Farmer?</h2>

    <!-- PHASE 2/3: real group photo goes here -->
    <div class="placeholder doctor-photo">
      [Group photo — Doctor Farmer with students / award]
    </div>

    <p>
      Doctor Prabhakar Raj has spent 8 years working with diabetic patients
      across Tamil Nadu. After watching the same patients return every few
      months with higher and higher dosages, he began asking a different
      question — not "how do we manage the sugar," but "why is it high in the
      first place, and can we fix that?"
    </p>
    <p>
      That question led to the founding of My Health School — through which he
      and his team have helped over 8,000 people across Tamil Nadu work toward
      reducing their sugar and their tablets. Not with new drugs. With a
      protocol built for reversing diabetes through simple, easy lifestyle
      changes.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <!-- =========================================================
       SECTION 6 — FAQ (native accordion)
       ========================================================= -->
  <section class="wrap" id="faq">
    <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>

    <div class="faq">
      <details>
        <summary>My diabetes is genetic — my father and grandfather had it.
                 Can it really be reduced?</summary>
        <div class="answer">
          Genetics affect how likely you are to develop diabetes. They do not
          decide whether it can be reduced. Some of the strongest results we've
          seen are in people with 20–30 years of family history. It means you
          need to be more consistent — not that it's impossible.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>I've tried everything — diet, exercise, supplements. Nothing
                 worked. Why is this different?</summary>
        <div class="answer">
          Because most approaches treat the symptom — the high sugar. This
          protocol addresses the three root causes: insulin resistance,
          inflammation, and a disturbed body clock. If those are never touched,
          the sugar always comes back. We address the root, not just the alarm.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>I'm a busy person. I don't have time for this.</summary>
        <div class="answer">
          Most of our people are working professionals and business owners who
          said the exact same thing. The daily practices take 15–20 minutes.
          The sessions are online. The protocol fits around your life — not the
          other way around.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Will I have to stop eating rice and Tamil food?</summary>
        <div class="answer">
          No. Our people still eat rice and Tamil food. What changes is the
          timing and structure — not the culture.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>What happens on the ₹99 assessment call?</summary>
        <div class="answer">
          The Doctor's senior health advisor will understand your situation —
          your sugar levels, your history, your daily life — and tell you
          honestly whether the program fits you. If it does, they explain how to
          start. If it doesn't, they tell you that, and your ₹99 is refunded.
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <!-- =========================================================
       SECTION 7 — FINAL CTA
       ========================================================= -->
  <section class="wrap final-cta" id="final">
    <h2>Your body can reduce the damage. The question is whether you'll give it
        the chance.</h2>

    <!-- PHASE 3 will wire this to the ₹99 booking form + Meta pixel / CAPI events.
         Non-functional for now. Keep id="cta-final". -->
    <a href="#" class="cta" id="cta-final">Book my health assessment — ₹99</a>

    <p class="caption risk-line">
      Fully refunded if you're not a fit. Our team will call you within 24 hours.
    </p>
  </section>

</body>
</html>
